---
---

<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Roadmap Ideas - What Mosaigo Pipelines Can Enable</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Explore the roadmap of project ideas built on mosaigo composable pipelines. From home surveillance to robotics, trading to content production."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/images/favicon-32x32.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/images/favicon-16x16.png" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/images/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/landing.css" />
    <style is:inline>
      .ideas-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(340px, 1fr));
        gap: 20px;
        max-width: 1200px;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }
      .idea-card {
        background: var(--bg-card);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 28px;
        transition: border-color 0.15s, transform 0.15s;
        text-decoration: none;
        color: inherit;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        text-align: left;
      }
      .idea-card:hover {
        border-color: var(--primary);
        transform: translateY(-2px);
      }
      .idea-card h3 {
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        color: var(--text);
      }
      .idea-card .idea-tagline {
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        flex: 1;
      }
      .idea-card .idea-tags {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 6px;
        margin-top: 16px;
      }
      .idea-card .idea-tag {
        font-size: 0.68rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        padding: 3px 10px;
        border-radius: 100px;
        background: rgba(42,127,191,0.1);
        color: var(--primary);
      }
      .idea-card .idea-tag.vision {
        background: rgba(200,152,42,0.1);
        color: var(--accent);
      }
      .idea-card .idea-tag.intelligence {
        background: rgba(58,143,92,0.1);
        color: var(--success);
      }
      .idea-card .idea-tag.community {
        background: rgba(109,179,224,0.1);
        color: var(--light);
      }
      .category-label {
        font-size: 0.72rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.14em;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        margin-bottom: 16px;
        padding-top: 20px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav class="topnav">
      <a href="/staging/" class="topnav-logo">
        <img src="/images/mozzy-icon.webp" alt="mosaigo" />
        mosaigo
      </a>
      <div class="topnav-links">
        <a href="/staging/" class="topnav-link">Staging</a>
        <a href="/getting-started/" class="topnav-link">Docs</a>
        <a href="/ideas/" class="topnav-link active">Roadmap Ideas</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-badge"><span class="dot"></span> Roadmap Ideas</div>
      <h1>What <span class="accent">mosaigo pipelines</span> can enable</h1>
      <p class="tagline">These are early-stage project concepts. Each one is a composable distribution built on mosaigo's pipeline engine, exploring a different domain. Nothing here is built yet. Everything is a direction worth exploring.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-centered">
      <div class="section-label">How to read this</div>
      <h2>Every idea starts with the same foundation</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Each project below reuses mosaigo's composable pipeline engine. Domain-specific steps snap into the same framework that powers mosoptics and mosii. The question isn't whether the plumbing works. It's which problems are worth solving first.</p>

      <div class="arch-visual" style="margin-top: 30px;">
        <div class="arch-layer accent">
          Roadmap Ideas <span class="desc">moshome, mospresent, mosbot, mosops, mostrade, depict, gtmd, storyarc, mosarch, sheetsync, teamtopo, gtmadvisor, aoc</span>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-arrow">all built on &#8595;</div>
        <div class="arch-layer primary">
          Staging Projects <span class="desc"><a href="/staging/" style="color:inherit;">mosaigo</a> + <a href="/staging/mosoptics/" style="color:inherit;">mosoptics</a> + <a href="/staging/mosii/" style="color:inherit;">mosii</a></span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-centered">
      <div class="category-label">Distributions (vision + control)</div>
      <div class="ideas-grid">
        <a href="/ideas/moshome/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>moshome</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Own your home cameras. Local-first, composable home surveillance with no subscriptions, no cloud lock-in. An open-source alternative to Ring, Nest, and Blink.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag vision">mosoptics</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">RTSP</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">local-first</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/ideas/mospresent/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>mospresent</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Virtual camera presentation tool. You become the content: slide elements float around you in a lightboard aesthetic. Gesture and voice drive navigation.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag vision">mosoptics</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">virtual camera</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">conferencing</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/ideas/mosbot/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>mosbot</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Composable robot control with real-time telemetry, safety-first design, and sim/real parity through pipeline graphs.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag vision">mosoptics</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">robotics</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">control</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/ideas/mosops/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>mosops</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Design-studio experience for building Kubernetes operators. Hot-reload steps while holding the leader lease. See what reconcilers actually do.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag">Kubernetes</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">operators</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">hot-reload</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/ideas/mostrade/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>mostrade</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Pipeline-based trading intelligence. Normalize feeds, compute signals, track portfolio. Human always decides on trades. Framework never auto-executes.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag">trading</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">signals</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">GraphQL</span>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="category-label" style="margin-top: 40px;">Intelligence (knowledge + content)</div>
      <div class="ideas-grid">
        <a href="/ideas/depict/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>depict</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Semantic ontology engine with GraphQL as the schema language. Provenance on every fact. Alignment as an explicit pipeline stage. The knowledge graph is alive.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag intelligence">foundation</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">GraphQL</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">ontology</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/ideas/gtmd/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>gtmd</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Go-to-market domain ontology. ICP, personas, positioning, messaging, funnels, and campaigns as data with provenance, not documents that drift.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag intelligence">depict module</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">GTM</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">marketing</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/ideas/storyarc/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>storyarc</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Content production from a graph. Story-arc templates with typed slots pull facts from depict/gtmd. LLM renders prose, not strategy.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag intelligence">depict module</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">content</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">templates</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/ideas/mosarch/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>mosarch</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Enterprise architecture as a typed graph. Decisions as first-class nodes. Per-stakeholder diagrams generated from one model.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag intelligence">depict module</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">architecture</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">diagrams</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/ideas/sheetsync/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>sheetsync</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Bidirectional sync between spreadsheets and the depict knowledge graph. Edit in a sheet, changes flow to the graph. Update the graph, changes appear in the sheet. Conflict-aware, provenance-tracked.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag intelligence">depict tool</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">sheets</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">bidirectional</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/ideas/teamtopo/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>teamtopo</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Team topologies as a live graph. Map team types, interaction modes, and RASCI roles. Define current state and target state. Track the transformation journey with Conway's Law alignment.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag intelligence">depict module</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">team topologies</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">RASCI</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/ideas/gtmadvisor/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>gtmadvisor</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Continuously-researching GTM knowledge graph. Learns from the best books and classics, tracks growth companies, analyzes moats and network effects, watches analyst signals. Applies general knowledge to your specific projects, products, and partners.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag intelligence">depict knowledge base</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">GTM strategy</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">moats</span>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="category-label" style="margin-top: 40px;">Community</div>
      <div class="ideas-grid">
        <a href="/ideas/aoc/" class="idea-card">
          <h3>aoc</h3>
          <p class="idea-tagline">Agent-managed open source. Agents in named roles keep the project alive: architecture, docs, evangelism, security, releases. Owners define what good looks like. Agents make it happen.</p>
          <div class="idea-tags">
            <span class="idea-tag community">community</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">agents</span>
            <span class="idea-tag">governance</span>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-centered">
      <div class="section-label">Shared dependencies</div>
      <h2>Three things every idea needs from the core</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">These are the load-bearing capabilities in mosaigo that all roadmap ideas depend on.</p>
      <div class="diff-grid" style="max-width:900px;margin:30px auto 0;">
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon primary">&#8644;</div>
          <h3>Hot-Swap Semantics</h3>
          <p>Swap pipeline steps at runtime without losing state. moshome, mospresent, mosbot, and mosops all depend on this capability.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon accent">&#9783;</div>
          <h3>Studio Visibility</h3>
          <p>The graphical differentiator that makes pipelines obviously better than logs. Every idea needs meaningful Studio visualization.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon success">&#128065;</div>
          <h3>mosoptics Foundation</h3>
          <p>Shared vision steps power the video-heavy distributions: moshome, mospresent, mosbot. These import mosoptics, not raw OpenCV.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta">
      <h2>Start with what's real</h2>
      <p>The ideas above are where we're headed. Below is what's being built right now.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/staging/" class="btn btn-primary">View Staging Projects</a>
        <a href="/getting-started/" class="btn btn-secondary">Read the Docs</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="footer">
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="/staging/">Staging</a>
        <a href="/getting-started/">Docs</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/mosaigoio">GitHub</a>
      </div>
      <p>&copy; 2025-present mosaigoio contributors</p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
